metadata.name: NAKACHOII #434
metadata.description:
*Nakachoii*
The Nakachoii soldiers from anime lands entered fxhash, this time to get new faces and new powers with the coding that is applied to them. Every time they are minted, and every time a new hash is generated, a new power is given to them. The Nakachoii soldier will fit inside your wallet and protect it with these powers. We are very happy that we gained so much experience on fxhash during its first year, and finally, we were able to create a great project based on all these experiences. Nakachoii is ready to create beauty.

metadata.name: Illuminations #47
metadata.description:
Created for the FxHash Turns One week - Thank you FxHash for all the opportunities you have given generative artists and collectors, and thank you to everyone who makes, and collects, the great art here. Here are a few celebratory generative effects which come from my 2022 experiments on random walks through color and space.

There are 5 different burst patterns (Whirligig, Sky Ripple, Confetti, Classic, Sparkler) and the Cocktail type brings them all together (somewhat chaotically)

To continue with the display after it stops press c

To switch to tranquil mode press t - You will want to try this out when you have a minute

To switch back to live mode press v

To stop the display process press x

To save a 2800x2800 jpg press s

Made with p5.js - all proceeds and royalties assigned to the Processing Foundation (who also deserve a big thank you)

This work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International License.

metadata.name: Ataraxis #134
metadata.description:
Ataraxis (or a broken volume renderer) is an exploration in balancing discomfort and calm. The piece generates spaces on the fly that are designed to elicit strange and uncomfortable feelings - like a desolate, alien dreamscape - claustrophobic, surreal, not quite real yet strangely recognisable. But the idea is that while these spaces feel uncomfortable, they're also strangely, antilogically calming. The idea is to elicit a sanguine emotion, to make the viewer feel calm in a strange place, and to lead them somewhere else.

This work is the culmination of many years of work researching volumetric rendering techniques. This token uses a raymarching technique that is intentionally broken in various ways.

Controls:
Double-click to download
&w=X&h=y to change the size of the piece
&dpr=x to change the resolution of the pice - higher resolutions will result in slightly different artworks as the browser attempts to compensate for the overlarge canvas
&fullscreen=true to change the token to display the full size of your browser. This may impact the rendering of the token, so use with caution

metadata.name: Fragment of Time #15
metadata.description:
"Year" is a mere four-letter word. But in reality, much has occurred. There are 12 months or approximately 365 days in a year. I joined fxhash about 4 months ago. And a lot has happened in my life since then. Can you imagine what happened to the people who founded, participated in, and maintained fxhash from its founding days? Everyday must've been different, and each day has its own pattern and color.

I've felt as if I lived in two different worlds since joining fxhash. I'm an architect by day, and a creator by night. I'm a part of fxhash, and I believe every single one of us experiences it that way. Each day has its own pattern and color.

This piece is my way of imagining what this community has gone through in a year. Each block represents a month from November 2021 to October 2022, with every block consists of smaller blocks that represents a day. Each of these days have their own colors and patterns. Every day tells its own story. But when you imagine a bigger picture of what happened in a year, you will see a specific pattern and color that you can keep as one big composition, and that gives you a year full of stories to admire.

I try to participate in the anniversary event as a way of expressing my gratitude. For everyone who has helped build this community so vibrant and meaningful - you have created such a world, and subsequently made my year. And therefore to me, you are all wonderful souls. So many artists, collectors, coders, art enthusiasts, and all of fxhash's teams have inspired me. Don't stop creating awesome stuff. Happy Birthday fxhash!!

metadata.name: Un1 #113
metadata.description:
Un1 is inspired by Unicode block element characters, and my love of minimal and monochromatic art. 

With Un1 I was looking for the final result to have a slightly degraded or low-res look. To that end the pixel density is intentionally set low, (saved images [s] will be based on your browser window size) so that when the piece is enlarged or printed the output has a degraded look.

This artwork was coded using the p5.js library
